According to the 

Heawood conjecture (formulated in 1890 by P.J. Heawood and proven in 1968 by Gerhard Ringel and J.W.T. Youngs), the chromatic number of a surface of genus g is\gamma(g) = \left\lfloor\frac{7+\sqrt{1+48g}}{2}\right\rfloor.

In particular, the torus has chromatic number \gamma(1)=7.

import numpy as np

from mpl_toolkits import mplot3d
import matplotlib.colors as mcolors
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
from matplotlib.colors import TABLEAU_COLORS, same_color
%matplotlib ipympl

R = 4
r = 1.33
w = .6
h = .6



